uccessful of all the Old French names of Germanic origin that were introduced to England by the Normans. It is derived from Germanic <i>wil</i> ‘will, desire’ + <i>helm</i> ‘helmet, protection’. The fact that it was borne by the Conqueror himself does not seem to have inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"William I Freford was born in 1240, in Staffordshire, England, United Kingdom. He had at least 1 son. He died in Freeford, Staffordshire, England, United Kingdom."},"et":{"1240–":"1240–Surnud","1265–1294":"1265–1294","1240–Male":"1240–Surnud","1265":"1265","1240":"1240","1294":"1294","Staffordshire, England, United Kingdom":"Staffordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Freeford,Staffordshire,England":"Freeford, Staffordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1240–":"1240–Kuollut","1265–1294":"1265–1294","1240–Male":"1240–Kuollut","1265":"1265","1240":"1240","1294":"1294","Staffordshire, England, United Kingdom":"Staffordshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Freeford,Staffordshire,England":"Freeford, Staffordshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1240–":"1240–Décédé","1265–1294":"1265–1294","1240–Male":"1240–Décédé","1265":"1265","1240":"1240","1294":"1294","Staffordshire, England, United Kingdom":"Staffordshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Freeford,Staffordshire,England":"Freeford, Staffordshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"William I Freford est né en 1240, à Staffordshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni. Il a eu au moins 1 fils. Il est décédé à Freeford, Staffordshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni."},"de":{"1240–":"1240–Verstorben","1265–1294":"1265–1294","1240–Male":"1240–Verstorben","1265":"1265","1240":"1240","1294":"1294","Staffo